speaker: Facebook posts
vclaim: “Arizona trooper found 50,000 ballots in dumpster all for President Trump!!”
date: stated on November 5, 2020 in a Facebook post:
title: No, Arizona troopers didn’t discover 50K ballots for Trump in a dumpster
text:
On Friday morning, Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden was leading in Arizona, where some news outlets had already declared the former vice president the winner. 
There were still 300,000 ballots remaining to be counted as an unnerving announcement started to spread on social media. 
"Arizona trooper found 50,000 ballots in dumpster all for President Trump!!" one Facebook post said. 
It was flagged as part of Facebook’s efforts to combat false news and misinformation on its News Feed. (Read more about our partnership with Facebook.) 

Featured Fact-check
















L. Lin Wood


stated on January 18, 2021 in an interview with the Patriotically Correct Radio Show








"China was behind the interference and the effort to overthrow our government and the election, election fraud."












By Daniel Funke • January 19, 2021







But we checked with the Arizona Department of Public Safety. and a spokesperson and sergeant there told us that, actually, troopers have not found 50,000 ballots for President Donald Trump. 
"It is not true," a sergeant said. 
We rate this Facebook post False.
